<subSubSection id="A7CC2DBDFFE3FFCBFF8DFB21FBADFE83" lastPageId="58" lastPageNumber="333" pageId="57" pageNumber="332" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="EF697E36FFE3FFCBFF8DFB21FBADFE83" blockId="57.[113,1089,1223,1566]" lastBlockId="58.[151,1127,220,339]" lastPageId="58" lastPageNumber="333" pageId="57" pageNumber="332">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFE3FFC8FF8DFB21FF5EFB6E" bold="true" box="[113,224,1223,1246]" pageId="57" pageNumber="332">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFE3FFC8FF18FB21FE6DFB6E" authorityName="Boheman" authorityYear="1862" box="[228,467,1223,1246]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Mesomphalia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="57" pageNumber="332" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="informis">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFE3FFC8FF18FB21FE6DFB6E" box="[228,467,1223,1246]" italics="true" pageId="57" pageNumber="332">Mesomphalia informis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was described presumably from a single specimen from the collection of J. S. Baly and so far was listed in catalogues only. 
<bibRefCitation id="8B4703C7FFE3FFC8FCE6FB01FC0FFB4E" author="SPAETH" box="[794,945,1255,1278]" firstAuthor="SPAETH" pageId="57" pageNumber="332" refId="ref50998" refString="SPAETH F. 1914: Chrysomelidae: 16. Cassidinae. In: SCHENKLING S. (ed.): Coleopterorum Catalogus. Pars 62. W. Junk, Berlin, 180 pp." type="book" year="1914">SPAETH (1914)</bibRefCitation>
transferred it to 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFE3FFC8FF72FAE1FED5FAAE" authorityName="Spaeth" authorityYear="1901" box="[142,363,1287,1310]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Pseudomesomphalia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="57" pageNumber="332" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFE3FFC8FF72FAE1FED5FAAE" box="[142,363,1287,1310]" italics="true" pageId="57" pageNumber="332">Pseudomesomphalia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(= 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFE3FFC8FE6EFAE1FE6DFAAE" baseAuthorityName="BOROWIEC" baseAuthorityYear="1999" box="[402,467,1287,1310]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Stolas" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="57" pageNumber="332" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFE3FFC8FE6EFAE1FE6DFAAE" box="[402,467,1287,1310]" italics="true" pageId="57" pageNumber="332">Stolas</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and 
<bibRefCitation id="8B4703C7FFE3FFC8FDEEFAE1FD68FAAE" author="BOROWIEC" box="[530,726,1287,1310]" firstAuthor="BOROWIEC" pageId="57" pageNumber="332" pagination="155 - 246" refId="ref48215" refString="BOROWIEC L. 1998 a: Review of the Cassidinae of Ecuador, with a description of thirteen new species. Genus 9: 155 - 246." type="journal article" year="1998" yearSuffix="a">BOROWIEC (1998a)</bibRefCitation>
to 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFE3FFC8FD05FAE1FCDBFAAE" authorityName="Chevrolat" authorityYear="1836" box="[761,869,1287,1310]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Cyrtonota" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="57" pageNumber="332" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFE3FFC8FD05FAE1FCDBFAAE" box="[761,869,1287,1310]" italics="true" pageId="57" pageNumber="332">Cyrtonota</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. This taxon belongs certainly to 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFE3FFC8FF0EFAC1FE8DFA8E" baseAuthorityName="BOROWIEC" baseAuthorityYear="1999" box="[242,307,1319,1342]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Stolas" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="57" pageNumber="332" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFE3FFC8FF0EFAC1FE8DFA8E" box="[242,307,1319,1342]" italics="true" pageId="57" pageNumber="332">Stolas</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as it has antennae only with four basal antennomeres shiny and sparsely pubescent while 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFE3FFC8FEDEFAA1FE30FAEE" authorityName="Chevrolat" authorityYear="1836" box="[290,398,1351,1374]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Cyrtonota" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="57" pageNumber="332" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFE3FFC8FEDEFAA1FE30FAEE" box="[290,398,1351,1374]" italics="true" pageId="57" pageNumber="332">Cyrtonota</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have five. It belongs to the 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFE3FFC8FD52FAA1FC58FAEE" authority="(Linnaeus, 1758)" baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1758" box="[686,998,1351,1374]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Stolas" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="57" pageNumber="332" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="discoides">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFE3FFC8FD52FAA1FC95FAEE" box="[686,811,1351,1374]" italics="true" pageId="57" pageNumber="332">S. discoides</emphasis>
(Linnaeus, 1758)
</taxonomicName>
speciesgroup and is very close to 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFE3FFC8FE7EFA81FE40FACE" baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1758" box="[386,510,1383,1406]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Stolas" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="57" pageNumber="332" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="discoides">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFE3FFC8FE7EFA81FE40FACE" box="[386,510,1383,1406]" italics="true" pageId="57" pageNumber="332">S. discoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
itself. The latter is a widely distributed species through tropical regions of America with numerous local geographical forms, often described as separate taxa and currently considered as synonyms. In 
<collectingCountry id="97C13EA6FFE3FFC8FD41FA41FCA8FA0E" box="[701,790,1447,1470]" name="Ecuador" pageId="57" pageNumber="332">Ecuador</collectingCountry>
there are at least two forms: montane, which is mostly black or dark metallic, and lowland Amazonian, which is bright metallic with red spots, quite similar to typical specimens from the Guyanas. 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFE3FFC8FC5DFA01FBFFFA4E" authorityName="Sekerka" authorityYear="2016" baseAuthorityName="Boheman" baseAuthorityYear="1862" box="[929,1089,1511,1534]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Stolas" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="57" pageNumber="332" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="informis">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFE3FFC8FC5DFA01FBFFFA4E" box="[929,1089,1511,1534]" italics="true" pageId="57" pageNumber="332">Stolas informis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is most similar to the montane form and recently described 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFE3FFCBFCF1F9E1FE80FF43" authority="Borowiec &amp; Takizawa, 2011" authorityName="Borowiec &amp; Takizawa" authorityYear="2011" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Stolas" kingdom="Animalia" lastPageId="58" lastPageNumber="333" order="Coleoptera" pageId="57" pageNumber="332" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="atalayaensis">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFE3FFC8FCF1F9E1FC0EF9AE" box="[781,944,1543,1566]" italics="true" pageId="57" pageNumber="332">S. atalayaensis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="8B4703C7FFE3FFCBFC46F9E1FE80FF43" author="Borowiec &amp; Takizawa" firstAuthor="Borowiec" lastPageId="58" lastPageNumber="333" pageId="57" pageNumber="332" pagination="427 - 484" refId="ref48679" refString="BOROWIEC L. &amp; TAKIZAWA H. 2011: Neotropical tortoise beetles in the Amazon Insectarium, Tokyo, Japan with description of nine new species (Coleoptera: Chrysomelidae: Cassidinae). Genus 22: 427 - 484." type="journal article" year="2011">Borowiec &amp; Takizawa, 2011</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
as it has large size and slightly indicated red reticulation in anterior third of explanate margin of elytra. However, 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFE0FFCBFDD9FF1AFD1CFEA3" baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1758" box="[549,674,252,275]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Stolas" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="58" pageNumber="333" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="discoides">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFE0FFCBFDD9FF1AFD1CFEA3" box="[549,674,252,275]" italics="true" pageId="58" pageNumber="333">S. discoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and similar species are in need of complex revision to set borders between taxa, therefore I leave 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFE0FFCBFD25FEFAFCF2FE83" authorityName="Sekerka" authorityYear="2016" baseAuthorityName="Boheman" baseAuthorityYear="1862" box="[729,844,284,307]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Stolas" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="58" pageNumber="333" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="informis">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFE0FFCBFD25FEFAFCF2FE83" box="[729,844,284,307]" italics="true" pageId="58" pageNumber="333">S. informis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a valid species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
